Done. Here's what changed and why:

**`pipeline_refactored.py`** — every original concern addressed:

| Original problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| Hardcoded paths, fake DB creds | `PIPELINE_LOG_FILE` / `PIPELINE_DB_PATH` env vars (real `DB_HOST`/`PORT`/`USER`/`PASS` were dead code — printed but never used by the SQLite code) |
| SQL injection (`%` formatting) | All queries use `?` parameterized placeholders via `execute` / `executemany` |
| Monolithic `proc_data()` | 10 well-named functions in **Extract** → **Transform** → **Load** phases |
| Fragile `.split(" ")` parsing | 4 compiled regex patterns (`_RE_ERROR`, `_RE_WARN`, `_RE_USER`, `_RE_API`) with named groups |
| No type hints / docs | Full `dataclass`, type annotations, and docstrings on every public function |
| No HTML escaping | `_html_escape()` prevents XSS in error messages or endpoint names |
| Manual `f.close()` | `with open(...)` context managers throughout |

